# Vocabulary

These definitions are exact. Do not under-scope or over-scope.

## Scope Commands

| Command | Scope |
|---|---|
| **"tidy"** / **"clean up"** | Current file only. Remove dead code, fix naming, inline trivial things. |
| **"refactor"** | Whole feature or module. Helpers, components, styles, structure, dedupe, file splits -- everything applicable. |
| **"aggressive refactor"** / **"deep refactor"** | Entire codebase. Every applicable category in `clean-code.mdc`. Still follow discipline rules. |

If the user says "refactor" and you only touch one category (e.g., styles), that is a failure. Cover every applicable category.

## Protocol Triggers

| Command | Action |
|---|---|
| **"rebuild"** | Follow `rebuild-protocol.mdc`. Keeps every feature, then rebuilds the app properly -- fixes messy structure, misplaced features, clashing modules, and misaligned CSS. Not a pixel copy of the old look. |
| **"redesign"** | Follow `redesign-protocol.mdc`. Changes how the app LOOKS and FEELS. Keeps core logic intact. Starts with a discovery conversation. |
| **"fix"** | Address a specific bug. Smallest possible change. |
| **"add"** | New feature. Follow existing patterns. |
| **"update"** / **"enhance"** | Extend an existing feature. |
| **"run autonomously"** | Follow `autonomous-mode.mdc`. |
| **"review"** | Follow `review-protocol.mdc` on the current state. |
| **"hotfix"** / **"production is broken"** | Follow `hotfix-protocol.mdc`. Fastest path: fix, test, deploy. |
| **"hand off"** / **"save state"** | Follow `session-handoff.mdc`. Write HANDOFF.md for the next session. |
| **"cleanup"** / **"clean up the codebase"** | Follow `cleanup-protocol.mdc`. Find and remove clutter: test artifacts, log files, cache files, old versions, dead exports. |
